    <string name="clipboard_permission_dialog_title">Grant system clipboard access</string>
    <string name="clipboard_permission_dialog_message">Android does not provide a unified runtime permission dialog for clipboard access. You usually need to manually allow this plugin in system app permissions or privacy settings. If your system provides options like “Read clipboard”, “Clipboard access”, or “Read clipboard in background”, enable them for ClipboardSync. It is also recommended to keep background running permission. Note: Android 10+ restricts clipboard reads when the app is neither foreground nor the default IME. This is platform policy, not a plugin bug. In this case, you can use “Capture and sync” from the notification for a one-time foreground capture.</string>
